For example, 
DLTensor* x;
int dtype_code = kFloat;
int dtype_bits = 32;
int dtype_lanes = 1;
int device_type = kCPU;
int device_id = 0;
TVMArrayAlloc(shape, 4, dtype_code, dtype_bits, dtype_lanes,
device_type, device_id, &x);
But If x is input, how to assign the array to x?

Thank you so much, @tqchen

I think TVMArrayAlloc is like tvm.placeholder,

  TVMArrayAlloc(shape, ndim, dtype_code, dtype_bits, dtype_lanes,
                device_type, device_id, &x);

 But why I cannot device_type set kGPU??
int device_type = kGPU;
